the report said the attacks occurred saturday night and sunday and that most were in the amritsar district, near the sikh holy city of amritsar
the victims included two hindus who were playing cards, three sikh communists and a sikh police constable, the news agency said. a sikh man and a woman whose identities were not known also died
the report gave no further details
uni said two sikh gunmen were killed in separate incidents
one was shot by police in the amritsar district sunday, uni said. it quoted police as saying the dead man was in a sikh group that attacked officers during a police raid on the village of chak mohar
the other was beaten to death by a farm family at nikahke village in the faridkot district saturday night. uni said the family was enraged when the gunman demanded their valuables
so far this year, police have blamed militant sikhs for the deaths of 430 people in punjab state, where sikhs are fighting for a separate homeland
sikhs are a religious minority in india and claim they are discriminated against by the hindu majority. sikhs are the majority in punjab state
